    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-09-27T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-09-27T20:00:00-05:00" n="800"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d800">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00112 European War 1939/143: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in the Netherlands</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gordon</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-09-27T20:00:00-05:00"
                            >September 27, 1939—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>100. Your 196, September 26, 11 a.m.<note n="40" xml:id="d800fn40">Not printed;
                        but see telegram No. 176, September 15, 5 p.m., from the Minister in the
                        Netherlands, <ref target="#pg_735">p. 735</ref>.</note> The whole shipping
                    question is in abeyance pending the outcome of the Congressional consideration
                    of the neutrality question. We had a preliminary and informal conversation with
                    the British regarding trade with neutral countries about 2 weeks ago but,
                    following the receipt of the British blockade note, it became necessary to
                    review the whole situation from the standpoint of our trade before resuming the
                    conversations. This review has now been completed and we expect to make in the
                    next day or so an oral statement to the British and to the diplomatic
                    representatives here of several neutral governments including the Netherlands.
                    We shall send you the substance of this statement as soon as <pb facs="0762"
                        n="750" xml:id="pg_750"/> it is made. You may communicate the foregoing to
                    the Foreign Minister in the strictest confidence.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
